# Storybook Story Rules

## Structure

Each component gets one story file in `stories/`. Use Storybook 10 + `@storybook/react-vite`:

```tsx
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from "@storybook/react-vite";
import { MyChart } from "../src/components/charts/MyChart";

const meta: Meta<typeof MyChart> = {
  title: "Charts/MyChart",
  component: MyChart,
  args: {
    height: 400,
    width: 600,
  },
};

export default meta;
type Story = StoryObj<typeof MyChart>;

export const Basic: Story = {
  args: {
    title: "Example Title",
    // provide realistic example data
  },
};
```

## Rules

- Import types from `@storybook/react-vite` (not `@storybook/react`)
- Set sensible default `height` and `width` in `meta.args`
- Use `argTypes` with `control: "select"` for enum props like `variant`
- Provide multiple named exports showing different use cases (Basic, WithCustomColors, Compact, etc.)
- Use realistic, meaningful example data — not placeholder values
- Every new chart component must have a story file
